cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with human pose estimation, which is a computer vision problem, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method that incorporates other cues from input features, which involves machine learning techniques such as Gaussian process regression, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of histograms of gradient features, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR. Finally, the paper deals with 3D pose estimation, which involves multimedia processing, making cs.MM a possible sub-category.
